<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Reconstruction Finance Corporation (RFC) was established by Hoover to:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Provide direct relief to unemployed workers</option>
            <option letter="b">Lend money to banks, railroads, and businesses</option>
            <option letter="c">Build public housing projects</option>
            <option letter="d">Fund agricultural subsidies</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Reconstruction Finance Corporation, created in 1932, was Hoover's major initiative to combat the Depression by providing government loans to banks, railroads, and other businesses. This reflected his belief in "trickle-down" economics, hoping that helping financial institutions would eventually benefit the general public, rather than providing direct aid to individuals.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
